# CODEOWNERS file for Application-X Infrastructure Repository
# 
# This file defines code owners for different parts of the repository.
# Code owners are automatically requested for review when someone opens a pull request
# that modifies files that they own.
#
# More info: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owners for everything in the repo
# These owners will be requested for review when someone opens a PR
* @engineering-team

# QA environment
# Requires QA team approval in addition to default
/envs/qa/ @qa-team @qa-lead

# Production environment
# Requires SRE/Platform team approval
# This is the critical gate for production changes
/envs/prod/ @sre-team @platform-team

# GitHub Actions workflows
# Any changes to CI/CD workflows require platform team review
/.github/workflows/ @platform-team @devops-lead

# CODEOWNERS file itself
# Changes to code ownership require leadership approval
/CODEOWNERS @engineering-manager @platform-lead

# Documentation
# Can be updated by anyone, but notify docs team
/*.md @docs-team

# Instructions for use:
# 1. Replace the team/user handles above with your actual GitHub team names or usernames
#    Example: @sre-team becomes @myorg/sre-team or @john-doe
# 
# 2. You can use GitHub teams (recommended) or individual users:
#    - Teams: @myorg/team-name
#    - Users: @username
#
# 3. Multiple teams/users can be specified for redundancy:
#    /envs/prod/ @sre-team @backup-sre-team
#
# 4. Configure branch protection rules in GitHub Settings to enforce these reviews
